<paragraph blockId="83.[151,1437,1975,2037]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">
Size. Maximum size about 
<quantity box="[457,512,1975,2001]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" unit="cm" value="3.0">3 cm</quantity>
total length. Morphology. D VI + I,6–7; A I,5–7; P 15. Body slender, laterally compressed. Head long, slightly depressed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="84" pageNumber="85" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="84.[151,1437,150,826]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,765,150,177]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">Snout pointed, equal to or longer than eye diameter</emphasis>
. S 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[795,1297,150,177]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">econd dorsal and anal fins with short base</emphasis>
and low ray counts (see fin meristics). Caudal peduncle slender, lower than body depth. Dorsal fins of similar height, first dorsal fin with more or less rounded margin. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[596,835,222,249]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">Caudal fin truncate</emphasis>
(Kovačić 
<emphasis box="[956,1007,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">et al</emphasis>
. 2016; Engin 
<emphasis box="[1172,1223,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">et al</emphasis>
. 2017; 
<bibRefCitation author="Kovacic, M. &amp; Glavicic, I." pageId="84" pageNumber="85" pagination="181 - 184" refId="ref58727" refString="Kovacic, M. &amp; Glavicic, I. (2019) The first Adriatic finding of Speleogobius llorisi (Actinopterygii: Gobiiformes: Gobiidae). Acta Ichthyologica et Piscatoria, 49 (2), 181 - 184. https: // doi. org / 10.3750 / AIEP / 02540" type="journal article" year="2019">Kovačić &amp; Glavičić 2019</bibRefCitation>
). Scales present on body and on predorsal area, poorly visible on photographs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="84.[151,1437,150,826]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">
Live coloration. The general hue may vary from beige to brown to reddish brown depending on the environment and the fish’s mood. Predorsal area reddish brown to whitish brown, 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">underside of head, cheek and opercle mostly red</emphasis>
with poorly visible white parts (Engin 
<emphasis box="[646,698,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">et al</emphasis>
. 2017), occasionally also yellowish (
<bibRefCitation author="Kovacic, M. &amp; Glavicic, I." box="[1124,1425,367,393]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" pagination="181 - 184" refId="ref58727" refString="Kovacic, M. &amp; Glavicic, I. (2019) The first Adriatic finding of Speleogobius llorisi (Actinopterygii: Gobiiformes: Gobiidae). Acta Ichthyologica et Piscatoria, 49 (2), 181 - 184. https: // doi. org / 10.3750 / AIEP / 02540" type="journal article" year="2019">Kovačić &amp; Glavičić 2019</bibRefCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,964,402,429]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">Three dark bars on dorsal half of body, alternating with 4 pale areas</emphasis>
, these 3 bars connected to 4 dark blotches on lower side of body, one more midlateral blotch on the posterior ventral part of caudal peduncle (
<bibRefCitation author="Duhau-Spielmann, M. &amp; Renoult, J. &amp; Louisy, P." pageId="84" pageNumber="85" refId="ref53650" refString="Duhau-Spielmann, M., Renoult, J. &amp; Louisy, P. (2021) Signalisation de / Record of Speleogobius llorisi, 04 January 2021 (obs. 03 September 2020, photo  5836). Fish Watch Forum, Louisy, P. &amp; Francour, P. (Ed.). Available from: https: // www. fishwatch. org (accessed 4 August 2021)" type="url" year="2021">
Duhau-Spielmann 
<emphasis box="[151,201,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">et al</emphasis>
. 2021
</bibRefCitation>
) (
<figureCitation box="[296,379,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="20.[151,250,980,1004]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,956]" captionTargetId="figure-19@20.[151,1436,181,956]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 13. Live coloration in its natural habitat of Speleogobius llorisi. Photo by R. Tournier-Broer, Saint-Raphaël, Southern France." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601605" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601605/files/figure.png" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[400,1074,474,501]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">Caudal peduncle uniformly pale dorsally, dark ventrally</emphasis>
. Dark bars and blotches may be quite diffuse in males, resulting in most of the body being rather uniformly dark, except caudal peduncle dorsally. Dorsal fins with a wide beige to whitish outer margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="84.[151,1437,150,826]" box="[199,654,583,609]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">
Similar species. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zander &amp; Jelinek" authorityYear="1976" box="[383,647,583,609]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Speleogobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="trigloides">
<emphasis box="[383,647,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">Speleogobius trigloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="84.[151,1437,150,826]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">
Habitat. Circalittoral species, known from 
<quantity box="[681,780,619,645]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.05" metricValueMax="6.9" metricValueMin="3.2" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" unit="m" value="50.5" valueMax="69.0" valueMin="32.0">32–69 m</quantity>
depth on rhodolith beds or detritic coarse sand and gravel (Kovačić 
<emphasis box="[265,318,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">et al</emphasis>
. 2016; Engin 
<emphasis box="[488,541,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">et al</emphasis>
. 2017; 
<bibRefCitation author="Kovacic, M. &amp; Glavicic, I." box="[634,936,655,681]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" pagination="181 - 184" refId="ref58727" refString="Kovacic, M. &amp; Glavicic, I. (2019) The first Adriatic finding of Speleogobius llorisi (Actinopterygii: Gobiiformes: Gobiidae). Acta Ichthyologica et Piscatoria, 49 (2), 181 - 184. https: // doi. org / 10.3750 / AIEP / 02540" type="journal article" year="2019">Kovačić &amp; Glavičić 2019</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Duhau-Spielmann, M. &amp; Renoult, J. &amp; Louisy, P." box="[951,1296,655,681]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" refId="ref53650" refString="Duhau-Spielmann, M., Renoult, J. &amp; Louisy, P. (2021) Signalisation de / Record of Speleogobius llorisi, 04 January 2021 (obs. 03 September 2020, photo  5836). Fish Watch Forum, Louisy, P. &amp; Francour, P. (Ed.). Available from: https: // www. fishwatch. org (accessed 4 August 2021)" type="url" year="2021">
Duhau-Spielmann 
<emphasis box="[1166,1219,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">et al</emphasis>
. 2021
</bibRefCitation>
; J. Renoult, unpublished observation).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="84.[151,1437,150,826]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">
Geographic distribution. Northern Mediterranean, presently known from the Balearic Islands (Kovačić 
<emphasis box="[1378,1429,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">et al</emphasis>
. 2016) to the Aegean Sea (Engin 
<emphasis box="[505,553,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">et al</emphasis>
. 2017), including 
<collectingCountry box="[753,829,763,789]" name="France" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">France</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Duhau-Spielmann, M. &amp; Renoult, J. &amp; Louisy, P." box="[842,1172,763,789]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" refId="ref53650" refString="Duhau-Spielmann, M., Renoult, J. &amp; Louisy, P. (2021) Signalisation de / Record of Speleogobius llorisi, 04 January 2021 (obs. 03 September 2020, photo  5836). Fish Watch Forum, Louisy, P. &amp; Francour, P. (Ed.). Available from: https: // www. fishwatch. org (accessed 4 August 2021)" type="url" year="2021">
Duhau-Spielmann 
<emphasis box="[1053,1101,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">et al</emphasis>
. 2021
</bibRefCitation>
; J. Renoult unpublished observation), 
<collectingCountry box="[305,370,799,825]" name="Malta" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">Malta</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kovacic, M. &amp; Schembri, P. J." box="[385,688,799,825]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" pagination="287 - 296" refId="ref58780" refString="Kovacic, M. &amp; Schembri, P. J. (2019) Twelve new records of gobies and clingfishes (Pisces: Teleostei) significantly increase small benthic fish diversity of Maltese waters. Mediterranean Marine Science, 20, 287 - 296. https: // doi. org / 10.12681 / mms. 19816" type="journal article" year="2019">Kovačić &amp; Schembri 2019</bibRefCitation>
) and the Adriatic Sea (
<bibRefCitation author="Kovacic, M. &amp; Glavicic, I." box="[943,1237,799,825]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" pagination="181 - 184" refId="ref58727" refString="Kovacic, M. &amp; Glavicic, I. (2019) The first Adriatic finding of Speleogobius llorisi (Actinopterygii: Gobiiformes: Gobiidae). Acta Ichthyologica et Piscatoria, 49 (2), 181 - 184. https: // doi. org / 10.3750 / AIEP / 02540" type="journal article" year="2019">Kovačić &amp; Glavičić 2019</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
